T|Cros|0|Both vt share the same pattern: an infrastructure exists but has not been operationalized. The analyst (ka) is fully defined — role, KPIs, alert thresholds, reporting cadence — but is starved of data bc the pipeline from source → sb → al was architected w/o being primed. For nz, this is a tactical gap (one ap call away from being resolved). For hb, it's a structural sequencing issue (pd must exist before data can flow). The common fix is the same: shift ka's posture from "wait for data" to "own the data pipeline." The ag.md routing table already assigns ka ownership of an, but ka needs operational authority to trigger data collection — not just consume it. dn (co) shd add "prime data pipelines" to the Monday checklist, and ka shd have direct access to the /ap/instagram and /ap/linkedin endpoints w/o routing through another ag.
